spring-test’s MockHttpServletRequest, which could introduce unnecessary dynamic access. I ponder whether this might impact coverage reports. Creating a custom minimal NativeWebRequest could cut down dependencies. But now I'm questioning whether using an existing public API like `constructAttribute` instead of `resolveArgument` could be more efficient, although it requires certain validations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring subclassing and method processing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using a subclass of `ModelAttributeMethodProcessor`, like `TestProcessor`, which has a public method that utilizes an internal path. I’ll need reflection to access the `EventForm` constructor. Although the `MethodParameter` is only needed for binding failure validation, it’s more focused now. The `constructAttribute` method is part of the public protected API since version 5.1. I wonder if I should create a minimal `NativeWebRequest` or use `ServletWebRequest` for simplicity. I need to be mindful of date conversions, as it may rely on field annotations.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active dynamic-access class.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `ModelAttributeMethodProcessorInnerFieldAwareConstructorParameterTest.java`\n  - Exercises constructor argument binding through `ModelAttributeMethodProcessor`.\n  - Uses a field-level `@DateTimeFormat` annotation so Spring must call `FieldAwareConstructorParameter.getParameterAnnotations()`.\n  - This reaches the remaining uncovered call site:\n    - `Class#getDeclaredField(String)` in `FieldAwareConstructorParameter`.\n\n- Updated `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-web/5.3.18/build.gradle`\n  - Added Spring context/test and servlet API test dependencies needed for formatting conversion and mock servlet request support.\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0379e235cfb612fb0169fff4a07d088193bb63729df8937069\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],